Text.Value: Keep quiet.
Good. Marshalling the goblins is no simple matter, but my warband will be ready to attack by next light.
Absolute be damned - Lolth is our goddess, and you are a heretic.
The Absolute has nothing to do with it. I'm here to kill you.
A duergar? Tell me, Sazza, did your misadventures take you to the Underdark?
A drow? Tell me, Sazza, did your misadventures take you to the Underdark?
Nah. Can't be... they woz in the grove, hangin' around with the tieflin's.
Fine.
I will gather my warband - we will reach the grove by next light.
Many of the inhabitants of the grove are already dead.
Return to the grove. When my raiding party approaches, throw open the gate and signal me.
Ah... well, the thing about that is... they sorta massacred us.
You only have to look at me to know I'm your superior, wretch.
I told ya! I was tryin' to follow orders best I could!
*You feel a cold hand caress your mind as the drow appraises you.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Camera cuts from player to drow as mindmeld occures

Text.Value: I want no part of this.
She's telling the truth. She didn't know.
I will gather my warband, and reach the grove by next light.
But we can still fight side by side. Together, we will destroy any who have not died or fled.
I presume you dealt with my prey, and massacred the rest?
Through sheer luck, that pathetic worm has brought me the information I need.
Silence, wretch. And remember - you owe your miserable life to this one.
You are a True Soul.
I'll get it done.
Take care of it quickly. You are needed here, and my patience wears thin.
You turned from Lolth for this Absolute. For that, you die.
You misunderstand. I'm here to slaughter you.
You are honoured to serve a cause - a god. What greater reward could there be?
And I'm happy to do it - for a price.
You coulda told me who you woz!
We are servants of the one true god, not mercenaries.

EditorData.stateContext: Sazza has been removed from the scene by guards or has left, unless the player pretended to be a True Soul at the checkpoint

Text.Value: The Absolute brought you here for a reason - to throw open those gates and crush our enemies.
There's a problem - the grove is sealed by a druid ritual.
A liar as well as a fool? I hope you're at least digestible.
You're right. Serving the Absolute is its own reward.
No! I mucked up, I'm sorry! But I didn't know who they woz... they didn't tell me nothin'!
And then the Absolute answered my prayers - sent a True Soul to save me!
*On the other hand, participating in the slaughter as she asks may be the perfect way to earn her trust, and access to the cult's inner circle.*
Mistress! It's me, yer loyal servant, Sazza. I'm back - an' I brought a friend.
Once we are in position, we will wait for your signal, and then we will break them all.
The Absolute will reward us.
You must make your way inside. Once I am in position, on your signal, we break them.
And it seems that the inhabitants of the grove trust you - we can use that against them.
You would dare...? Guards - to me!
And it will be your last. My spiders are hungry, little one...
I do not intend to lead a suicidal charge. The goblins are expendable; I am not.
All right. Expect me at the grove.
Excellent. When you give the signal, we will break them. The Absolute will reward us.
I won't be much use to the cause if I'm destitute.
It's past the bridge, to the east! Big ol' gate, covered in ivy! Don't hurt me, mistress. Please!
Kill our enemies, and take what you need.
*Killing the drow here would spare them, but it might be better to face her warband at the grove itself, on familiar ground.*
Undercover, no doubt. Carrying out the Absolute's will. Oh, Sazza - you have made a grave error.
Oh dear. Your prisoner is one of the Absolute's favourites, Sazza. A True Soul.
I got myself nabbed though; ended up all snug in a cage instead of smashed. I'm wily like that.
How thoughtful. And where did you find this friend?
...but before they feast, tell me where that grove is, and I may yet spare your life.
You have a part to play in this slaughter.
*The fate of the grove's inhabitants hangs in the balance.*
Gold, and lots of it.
They woz in some rickety druid grove! Mostly full of tieflin's, but them intruders you're after were hidin' out there!
It ain't true! Them's the bloody liars!
I will not hurt you. My spiders will have that pleasure.
I won't cause any more trouble - I swears it.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: [reuse] The captured goblin scuttles away. [Hide Sazza after walk off]

Text.Value: Their god is weak. Roots and branches will not save them from the Absolute's fury.
I explained everything to her. She's just too stupid to understand.
Praise be to Her!
I have another matter to take care of first.
But this mug helped me to escape. I say we stick a few holes in him... show how grateful we are.
This mug helped me to escape though. I say we stick a few holes in her... show how grateful we are.
This mug helped me escape though. I say we stick a few holes in them... show how grateful we are.
You started the slaughter without me? How selfish.
Somebody help!

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Sazza]  looks around panicked while asking for help <AaronH>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: ~The captured goblin is dragged away by goblin guards. [Hide Sazza after walk off]

Synopsis:
The players approach the drow commander at the goblin camp, escorted by a goblin who they rescued from a nearby druid grove. The drow is seeking that grove and upon learning its location from the goblin will prepare to raid it, demanding that the player help.

If the goblin recognises that the player is a True Soul - a figure of authority - her life will be spared. If she does not recognise this, the drow will execute her unless the player intervenes on her behalf.
